  "text": "Then the matching flower of z (w.r.t. (ϕ, ψ)) is defined by F (ϕ, ψ, z) := F c , where the union is over all competing chains c for z. This definition is similar to (2.1) in [CITATION_1] . Just for completeness we define F (ψ, ϕ, z) := {z} for z / ∈ ϕ ∪ ψ.",
